<@U05777BLCPN>  <@U057J8HJZMF> <@U0574SA4NJ2> Hey team, I think I have an idea for a game plan. We should prioritize making sure we hit the minimum requirements for the project: External API :white_check_mark:, Relational Database :white_check_mark:, CRUD functionality:x: , and Authentication :x:

We still need to finish hooking up authentication + the frontend CRUD functionality to satisfy the minimum requirements of the project. To do that, I think we should:

1. Create Add to Watchlist and Remove from Watchlist button components that we can put into a movie card.
2. Make buttons on the profile page that let us Create a new watchlist, Delete a Watchlist, And Update the Name of a watchlist, since that controller is already done.
3. Finalize updating the Authentication Controller to be connected to the front end.
I know it's fast, but we should try to get all this done by *today*, or at least by tomorrow. After that, Cory recommended we try to meet with Colin on Monday to talk about what can be done next to make sure we all get our three features.
